<subSubSection id="8C8E6575FF206A9FFD1C974B1B2BB95C" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="C42B36FEFF206A9FFD1C974B1B2BB95C" blockId="219.[733,1328,274,701]" pageId="219" pageNumber="981">
Subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC7D974B1DD5BA01" authority="Kaup, 1829" box="[897,981,274,307]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Myotis</taxonomicName>
; 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC09974B1A42BA01" authorityName="Borkhausen" authorityYear="1797" box="[1013,1090,274,307]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Vespertilio" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="myotis">myotis</taxonomicName>
species group. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFD1D97601DBEBA68" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1908" box="[737,958,313,346]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pequinius">Myotis pequinius</taxonomicName>
appears to be related to M. 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFCE697381D92BAB0" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1906" box="[794,914,353,386]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="bombinus">bombinus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFC1197381A8EBAB0" baseAuthorityName="Kuhl" baseAuthorityYear="1817" box="[1005,1166,353,386]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="981" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="nattereri">M. nattereri</taxonomicName>
tschuliensis based on limited genetic data. There might be at least two species under 
<taxonomicName id="03944D7DFF206A9FFB2297F61D42BACA" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1908" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="219" pageNumber="980" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pequinius">M. pequinius</taxonomicName>
as currently defined, based on genetic data showing that there are two highly divergent clades within the species. Additional studies are needed. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
